  "summary": "phpMyFAQ: Stored XSS in FAQ Question/Answer via Encode-Decode Bypass of removeAttributes() Sanitization",
  "details": "phpMyFAQ before 4.1.2 contains a stored cross-site scripting vulnerability in FAQ creation and update endpoints that bypass sanitization through encode-decode cycles. The vulnerability allows authenticated attackers with FAQ_ADD permission to inject malicious script tags via question or answer parameters, which execute in every visitor's browser when FAQ content is rendered with the raw Twig filter.",
